The paper deals with the nearest common ancestor (NCA) function in rooted trees, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. This suggests that the paper belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The paper also introduces universal trees for the NCA function, which is a concept related to graph theory and combinatorics. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
